overview: Woodstock '99 was the second large-scale music festival (after Woodstock '94) that attempted to emulate the original Woodstock festival of 1969.  Day 1 (July 23, 1999) features performances by Oleander, G Love and Special Sauce, The Umbillical Brothers, MOE., Jamiroquai, Lit, Live, Buckcherry, Sheryl Crow, The Roots, DMX, The Offspring, Insane Clown Posse, Korn, and George Clinton & The P Funk Allstars.
title: Woodstock '99: Day 1
